Content: An office manager is ordering this year’s supply of pencils and pens for the office. Each pencil costs $0.10, each pen costs $0.75, and the manager will spend a total of $235 on pencils and pens.

A.Choice: The number of pencils purchased last year will be equal to the number of pens purchased this year.

B.Choice: The number of pens purchased this year will be three times the number of pencils purchased this year.

C.Choice: The total cost of the pens purchased this year will be greater than the total cost of the pencils purchased this year.

D.Choice: The total cost of the pencils and pens purchased last year will be three times the total cost of the pencils and pens purchased this year.
